news.title: India's Grade A office market is likely to touch 1.2 billion sq ft by 2030: JLL
news.para: As such, the flex market is expected to double its footprint across the top seven cities by 2025 to about 75 million sq ft and cross the 100 million sq ft mark by 2030.

news.title: Focus on Noida airport, Yeida unveils draft master plan 2041
news.para: While Yeida-notified area covers about 2,689 sq km falling in six districts, this master plan is focused on Phase 1 of the notified area covering 171 villages and an area of 604 sq km.

news.title: Brookfield entity Sagen acquires 31% stake in IMGC
news.para: The proceeds will provide growth capital to the business and support the enhancement of operational and technological capabilities while maintaining a robust risk management framework.

news.title: Bengaluru: 91% land for Silk Board Metro acquired
news.para: ​BMRCL sources say that 91.28 per cent of land required for 2A and 2B phases have been acquired. There will be 30 stations on the 58.19 km stretch. The estimated cost for completing this stretch is Rs 14,788.10 crore.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 58 acres of land in Nagpur
news.para: The development on this land will comprise primarily of plotted residential units and will offer an estimated saleable area of 1.5 million sq. ft.

news.title: Rajasthan: Over 580 families get property rights under Svamitva scheme
news.para: The central sector scheme Svamitva aims to provide the ‘record of rights’ to village household owners possessing houses in inhabited areas of villages with issuance of legal ownership rights including property cards and title deeds.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram witnesses a surge in property registrations
news.para: The government exchequer has earned Rs 560.67 crore through registration fee and stamp duty from these registrations. While Rs 413.56 crore was the stamp duty earned (at eight per cent of the registration value), Rs 147.10 crore was earned as the registration fee (at two per cent of the property value).

news.title: About 1.2 lakh housing sites to be distributed in Visakhapatnam today
news.para: Chief Minister YS Jagan Mohan Reddy will formally distribute the pattas in a public meeting that will be organised in Pydivada Agraharam village in Sabbavaram mandal on Thursday.

news.title: Nagpur: Consumer forum awards three years jail to builders
news.para: A bench comprising president Sanjay Patil and members Smita Chandekar and Avinash Prabhune also directed the builders to pay Rs 25,000 fine each and in case of default they will remain further six months behind bars.

news.title: Haryana RERA to formulate guideline for handing over of projects to RWAs
news.para: The authority in partnership with other departments is organising a conclave on RWAs to make them aware of the existing Act.

news.title: Noida: Twin towers demolition to be pushed back by two months?
news.para: The uninhabited towers, Ceyane and Apex, at Emerald Court have a tentative demolition date of May 22. The Supreme Court ordered both towers to be razed last August, ruling they were built in violation of law.

news.title: SC gives chance to Unitech buyers who are senior citizens, persons in medical need to seek refund
news.para: The Unitech board of management informed the top court that subject to statutory approvals and availability of funds, it will be able to deliver 1000 to 1500 flats in nine to 12 months starting from August, this year.

news.title: Ideal Cures' founder buys Rs 64-crore luxury pad in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: Pareek has bought the apartment on the 12th floor of an under-construction project Raheja Artesia being developed by realtor K Raheja Corp Homes. The buyer has paid nearly Rs 3.23 crore as stamp duty for the registration of the agreement.

news.title: Nandan Nilekani's NRJN Family Trust buys property worth Rs 58 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The purchase involves a 9,600 sq ft property with a built-up area of over 3,000 sq. ft. in Koramangala 3rd block. The deal was registered on April 19 and a stamp duty of Rs 2 crore was paid as per the registry document shared by ZapKey.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace posts profit of Rs 154.5 crore in FY22
news.para: Arvind Subramanian, Managing Director and CEO, Mahindra Lifespace Developers Ltd, said, "FY22 has been a year of strong growth. Our residential pre-sales grew by almost 50 per cent to Rs 1,028 crore while our industrial leasing has grown by 130 per cent to Rs 298 crore".
